-- ============================================================================
-- IMPORTANT NOTE ON AVERAGES
-- ============================================================================
/*
KEY CONCEPT: Why averages match when properly aggregated

The merged query stores granular metrics at the most detailed level
(PAYOUT_TYPE + CHANNEL + PPT_BUCKET + DIRECTION).

When you roll up to a higher level, you need to use WEIGHTED AVERAGES:
- Correct: SUM(TOTAL_PRINCIPAL) / SUM(TOTAL_TXNS)
- Incorrect: AVG(AVG_PRINCIPAL)

Example:
  Group A: 100 txns, avg principal = $200
  Group B: 10 txns, avg principal = $1000
  
  Correct overall average = (100*$200 + 10*$1000) / (100+10) = $272.73
  Incorrect average = ($200 + $1000) / 2 = $600

The verification queries above use the correct weighted average approach,
so they should match the individual dimension queries exactly.

To get the same results from the merged table at any aggregation level:
1. SUM the totals (TOTAL_TXNS, TOTAL_PRINCIPAL, TOTAL_REVENUE, etc.)
2. Divide SUM(TOTAL_PRINCIPAL) / SUM(TOTAL_TXNS) to get AVG_PRINCIPAL
3. Never use AVG(AVG_PRINCIPAL) - this will give incorrect results!
*/


